The paper deals with dynamic graph algorithms in the Massively Parallel Computation model, which is a topic related to distributed computing (cs.DC) and graph algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the Minimum Spanning Forest and Maximal Matching problems, which are classic problems in graph theory (cs.DM). The algorithms presented in the paper are designed to work in a memory-restricted environment, which is a topic related to computational complexity (cs.CC) and machine learning (cs.LG).
